[SIZE=28px][B]go-udap v2.4.0 is available[/B][/SIZE]

[URL="https://github.com/yo61/go-udap/releases/tag/v2.4.0"]Get it on the GitHub release page[/URL] — or [FONT=Courier New]brew upgrade go-udap[/FONT] if you installed via Homebrew.

[SIZE=20px][B]What's new since v2.3.0[/B][/SIZE]

[B]Man pages.[/B] Release archives now ship [FONT=Courier New]go-udap.1[/FONT] plus one page per subcommand — [FONT=Courier New]man go-udap[/FONT], [FONT=Courier New]man go-udap-set[/FONT], and so on. They're generated from the command tree, so flags and defaults stay in lockstep with the binary. Homebrew users get them registered on the next [FONT=Courier New]brew upgrade[/FONT]; from a tarball, drop [FONT=Courier New]share/man/man1/*.1[/FONT] anywhere on your [FONT=Courier New]MANPATH[/FONT].

[B]Refreshed README and [URL="https://yo61.github.io/go-udap/"]docs landing[/URL].[/B] The opening paragraph now states plainly what go-udap is and what it replaces — one static binary, no Lyrion Music Server required for setup, no Perl, no GUI — followed by a feature list and a realistic quick-start session.
